Detailed Description

The meta informations of a connection stored in the main Binary Tree.

conn_struct

Parameters:
key,the tuple (also the b-tree key)
key_ext,the IP and Port of the external attacker
key_lih,the IP and Port of the Low Interaction Honeypot
key_hih,the IP and Port of the High Interaction Honeypot
protocol,the l4 protocol number (6 for TCP, 17 for UDP, ...)
access_time,the last access time
status,the status of the connection: (1) for INIT, (2) for DECISION, (3) for REPLAY and (4) for FORWARD. (0) can mean INVALID
count_data_pkt_from_lih,nb of packet replied from the lih to the intruder
count_data_pkt_from_intruder,nb of packet sent from the intruder to the LIH
BUFFER,pointer to the beginning of the list of the recorded packets (stored through pkt_struct)
lock,set to 1 when a packet is currently processed for this connection
hih,hih info
